m>: Two years after Grant Hill retired from the NBA, he bought an ownership=
 stake in the Atlanta Hawks. He=E2=80=99s since grown his portfolio to incl=
ude
stakes in the Baltimore Orioles, Orlando City SC, and Orlando Pride. On thi=
s week=E2=80=99s <em>Varsity </em>podcast, I asked about his path to owners=
hip. Hill referenced his father, NFL great <strong>Calvin</strong> <strong>=
Hill</strong>, a Super Bowl champion running back and successful sports bus=
iness executive who tried unsuccessfully to buy stakes in various teams ove=
r the years. =E2=80=9CAt an early age, being aware of that pursuit, and bei=
ng aware of that possibility, it just planted a seed,=E2=80=9D Hill told
me. =E2=80=9CI thought, <em>I=E2=80=99d like to do that one day</em>. <em>I=
 don=E2=80=99t want to run a team. I want to own a team</em>. I was not exa=
ctly sure how it would happen, but I spent time cultivating relationships a=
nd spent time with the numerous owners that I played with.=E2=80=9D<br/><br=
/>Hill was part of a group that bid on the Los Angeles Clippers in 2014 but=
 lost out to <strong>Steve Ballmer</strong> by about <em>$500 million</em>.=
 A year later, Hill was part of the group, led by Apollo co-founder <strong=
>Tony
Ressler</strong>, that bought the Hawks. =E2=80=9CThat wasn=E2=80=99t somet=
hing where I retired and decided to pursue it,=E2=80=9D Hill said. =E2=80=
=9CI started pursuing that in 1996.=E2=80=9D</li><li style=3D"Margin:0 0 24=
px 0;"><em>LIV vs. PGA Tour</em>: Even with its new multiyear rights deal w=
ith Fox, LIV Golf has failed to make it out of the rough. To wit: The PGA T=
our=E2=80=99s Phoenix Open drew more than 2 million viewers on February 9, =
per Nielsen research. The same day, the LIV tournament from Riyadh attracte=
d just
54,000 Nielsen viewers.<br/><br/>Still, keep an eye on April 6, the last da=
y of the PGA Tour=E2=80=99s Valero Texas Open in San Antonio, which will be=
 carried on NBC. The same day, Fox will carry a LIV Golf tournament from Tr=
ump National Doral in Miami. With many PGA Tour players expected to sit out=
 the Valero Open to prepare for the Masters, which starts April 7 in August=
a, this may be the Saudi-backed LIV=E2=80=99s best chance to post TV rating=
s on par with the PGA Tour.</li></ol></div>
